 Sahara reporters publisher and 2019 presidential aspirant, Omoyele Sowore has opened up about his ordeal with the Nigerian government and Senate president, Bukola Saraki over his continued exposure of corruption. Sowore, while speaking at a town hall meeting in Owerri, Imo state recently, revealed that the Nigerian government seized all his assets. He disclosed that the Senate president, Bukola Saraki, obtained a court order to freeze his bank accounts, seizing over $200,000. The townhall monitored by PoliticsNGR was a successful one as Sowore detailed his plans for the various regions of the country. He also attacked the government over its incompetence and failure to perform.